    "client_msg_id": "6dc5acae-e8b4-4bd0-8ba3-074cd6d38fa2",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Also the phrase '1% of the possible performance' - I don't think is necessarily bad. Many cars do run at a small percentage of the 'possible performance', for some value of performance, when you compare them to Formula 1, for instance. The overarching driving forces are mainly economic and based on the context of the problem being solved.",
