  {
    "client_msg_id": "01255470-413a-4484-b3b2-75ed731ed732",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "One word: externalities. One sophont's delivery is not another one's problem.\n\nI think I already shared this link in an earlier thread: <http://250bpm.com/blog:51>\n\nSoftware is memes (in the original Richard Dawkins sense) made manifest.\n\nThe only way out of this asylum is to take control of your stack. At all levels. But alas I don't know how to make that actionable yet.\n\nThere's a very great danger that in a couple of generations kids will think software is as hard to change as atoms. No more over-the-air updates, too insecure and too hard to regulate.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1537888899.000100",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
